                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Amazon.com:</DIV>
                <span id="Label1">Being your own boss, as anyone who's tried it can attest, is not as easy as it looks. The rewards can be great, but hurdles abound--and many fledgling entrepreneurs never manage to get beyond the latter in order to enjoy the former. Well-known experts Sarah and Paul Edwards believe it can be done, though, and present solid tips for thriving as well as surviving in <b>Secrets of Self-Employment</b>, an expanded version of one of their popular early works.  </span>
              
