                    <span>I am 21 years old, and would love to be a part time real estate investor and be an independent personal trainer!  I am in college, and have had low paying minimum wage jobs(working for someone else) and my LONG TERM goal is  to be my own boss.  Why spend your whole life working under 1 person's  clock, with only one set paycheck(a lousy one at that) when you are capable  of so much more?   To me having your paycheck dependent upon only one  person is much riskier than getting the same amount if not more from lots  of other people.  All of the males in my father's side of the family worked  for themselves.  Here is what my great-great grandfather once told my own  father, "It is best to get $1 from 100 people, then to get $100 from  only one person".</span>
                  
              
